    <text>
        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)">
                <placeName>243 Broadway</placeName>
            </p>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>NY</placeName>
                <date>Oct. 25. 5630</date>.</p>
            <p>My dear Sir,</p>
            <p>1<hi rend="sup">st</hi> Whenever you revisit <placeName>N.Y.</placeName><lb/>
                <persName>Mrs. I.</persName> &amp; self will be pleased to see<lb/> you at our home
                    <placeName>239 West 52<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> Street</placeName>.</p>
            <p>2<hi rend="sup">nd</hi> “<persName>Patrick</persName>” in print looks<lb/> acceptable
                and the portraits as l<add>?</add>ed<lb/> bear <hi rend="underline">some</hi>
                resemblance to “actualities”<lb/> for instance, <persName>Vielsprach</persName> =
                    <persName>Huebsch</persName> or <persName>Sonnen<lb/>schein</persName> of
                    <placeName>N.Y.</placeName>?</p>
            <p>3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi> Lives there a Jew<lb/> with soul so great<lb/> That really to
                himself did state,<lb/>
                <persName>Mamonides</persName> I will endow?<lb/> Is there,
                    <persName>Patrick</persName>, tell we now?</p>
            <p>For a Yankee in <placeName>Mass.</placeName> has since $40000.<lb/> for the Hebrew
                Professorship at <placeName>Andover</placeName>!</p>
            <p>4<hi rend="sup">th</hi> Yr Rabbis will meet at
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName><lb/> on the <date>3<hi rend="sup">rd</hi></date>
                Proxo. Can you pass yourself</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p>off as a newly arrived Ph. Dr. anxious<lb/> to hear <persName>Adler</persName>,
                    <persName>Hirsch</persName>, <persName>Einhorn</persName> fight<lb/> it out on
                their line? Or can you<lb/> listen at the keyhole &amp; tell us what<lb/> they say
                &amp; do? They propose to<lb/> sit with “closed doors” &amp; not let<lb/> the
                messenger in. Can we circum<lb/>vent them &amp; is it worth while?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Our printer made a little blunder<lb/> in the last # of the
                Patrician sh<add>?</add><lb/> in <date>Friday's</date> messenger? Forgive him?</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">Please let me know how the<lb/> College progresses. I hear
                nothing<lb/> about it.</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">Truly Yours,</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">
                <persName role="author">M. J. Isaacs</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="The following is written upside down at the bottom right corner of the page."/>
            <p>
                <persName role="author">M. J. Isaacs</persName>
            </p>
            <p><date>Oct. 25. 1869</date>.</p>
        </body>
